parameters:
\n<Rui>So this lever is the switch for the large
ventilation fan.

\n<Rui>...This panel was also by the school entrance.
That means, to get out of the entrance...
this.PLLightOn("white" , 30); //プレイヤーのライトをつける

\n<Rui>The angle of this hole... Falling here would
definitely be bad.\C[10] I need to be careful not
to step off.

\n<Mechanical Voice>Insufficient voltage for the elevator. Please cut
the power to unnecessary facilities inside the
room.

\n<Rui>I see... I've seen something like this in escape
games before.
\n<Rui>There are four more power levers to go, it seems.

\n<Mechanical Voice>The elevator is currently charged to 20%. Once
charging is complete──

\n<Rui>Ah... so it's an escape, but from a horror
scenario.

\n<Rui>Restore power to the elevator and escape from the
monster.
\n<Rui>...It's just that when you put it into words.

\n<Rui>No... really... being in that situation is...
tough...

\n<Rui>Ah, I've decided. I'm absolutely never going to a
haunted house again...!

\n<Rui>This is the time to be brave... I can't be shaking
when the goal is in sight!
this.PLLightOn("white" , 30); //プレイヤーのライトをつける
\n<Rui>...Couldn't this slope be a bit gentler?

events.name: リージョンイベント発生

parameters: this.PLLightOn("white1" , 30); //プレイヤーのライトをつける

\n<Rui>The angle of this hole... Falling down there would
be bad news. \C[10]I need to be careful not to
slip.

\n<Mechanical Voice>Insufficient voltage for the lift. Please cut any
unnecessary power inside the room.

\n<Mechanical Voice>The lift is currently at 1% charge. Once charging
is complete──

\n<Rui>I see... So it's like an escape from a horror
scenario.

\n<Rui>Stuck in this cramped space, running from monsters
until the elevator's power is restored... It's a
classic.

\n<Rui>Well, the situation at hand is... really something
I could do without.

\n<Rui>Ahh, that's it... I've decided. I'm absolutely
never going to a haunted house again.

\n<Rui>This is the time to be brave... I can't be shaking
when the goal is in sight!
\n<Rui>As if I'd let myself get caught!
